article.headline: Prairie View 67, Jackson State 64
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas (AP) -- Tyrone Nelson had 24 points and 12 rebounds and Kevin Cooper scored 16 points as Prairie View beat Jackson State 67-64 Saturday night. Roderick Riley added 13 points and eight rebounds for Prairie View (5-15, 5-6 Southwestern Athletic), which led for most of the game. Ishmael Joyce scored 20 points and Antonio Williams-Parker had 16 for Jackson State (10-11, 9-4). K.C. Cavette added 14 points. Prairie View led 37-28 at halftime then held on despite hitting just 35 percent from the field in the second half. Prairie View dominated inside, with a 39-26 rebounding advantage and a 30-22 edge in scoring in the paint.
